earned%20to%20choose%20my%20TV%20shows%20very%20carefully.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EI'm%20a%20librarian%20and%20feel%20like%20I%20have%20to%20read%20everything%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20can't%20choose%20books%20the%20same%20way.%20I%20am%20a%20writer%2C%20but%20I%20am%20also%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwork-decimated-office-socializing-the-solution-could-be-libraries-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ea%20librarian%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Reading%20is%20my%20literal%20job.%20I%20have%20to%20keep%20up%20with%20trends%20so%20I%20can%20see%20how%20my%20writing%20can%20enter%20the%20conversation%3B%20I%20need%20to%20know%20about%20all%20the%20new%20books%20so%20I%20can%20make%20apt%20recommendations%20to%20my%20patrons.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThough%20my%20demurely-titled%20%26quot%3BReading%20List%26quot%3B%20started%20with%20those%2050%20books%20I%20just%20had%20to%20read%20in%20my%2020s%2C%20it%20soon%20ballooned%20to%20include%20award-winners%20from%20each%20new%20year%2C%20collections%20from%20%26quot%3BBest%20Of%26quot%3B%20lists%2C%20and%20occasionally%2C%20a%20book%20that%20I%20might%20actually%20like%20to%20read.%20Ten%20years%20later%2C%20the%20list%20had%20grown%20to%20include%20over%20500%20titles%2C%20and%20I%20had%20become%20strangely%20bound%20to%20it%2C%20only%20allowing%20myself%20to%20read%20titles%20from%20the%20list%20(and%20occasionally%20sneaking%20new%20things%20on%20that%20I%20desperately%20wanted%20to%20read%20just%20to%20follow%20my%20own%20arbitrary%20rules).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIntellectually%2C%20I%20understood%20that%20this%20was%20madness.%20But%20by%20then%2C%20I%20had%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdecided-raise-kids-family-near-grandparents-pros-and-cons-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emoved%20away%20from%20my%20family%3C%2Fa%3E%20into%20a%20new%20city%20in%20a%20new%20state.%20I%20found%20our%20country%20to%20be%20a%20monumental%20disappointment%20in%20more%20ways%20than%20one.%20A%20pandemic%20had%20begun%2C%20and%20made%20time%20contract%20and%20expand%20in%20unexplainable%20ways.%20We%20were%20already%20living%20in%20madness%2C%20so%20what%20was%20so%20wrong%20about%20me%20escaping%20into%20the%20madness%20of%20believing%20I%20would%20ever%20reach%20the%20end%20of%20this%20list%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20list%20was%20a%20comfort.%20I%20didn't%20have%20to%20decide%20what%20to%20do%20next%20%E2%80%94%20in%20some%20ways%2C%20having%20a%20list%20felt%20like%20a%20way%20of%20maintaining%20a%20sense%20of%20order.%20I%20could%20go%20down%20it%2C%20one%20by%20one%2C%20filling%20my%20creative%20mind%20with%20all%20the%20recommended%20reads%20of%20the%20last%2010%20years.%20I%20kept%20track%20on%20my%20Goodreads%20account%2C%20attempting%20to%20complete%20a%20challenge%20of%20reading%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2F10-best-non-fiction-books-of-2020-coronavirus-reading-time-2020-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E100%20books%20a%20year%3C%2Fa%3E%20(a%20number%20I%20never%20actually%20met%20that%20made%20me%20feel%20like%20a%20woeful%20failure%20come%20each%20December).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20learned%20my%20habits%20might%20be%20due%20to%20OCD%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20have%20seen%20a%20handful%20of%20therapists%20about%20my%20habit%20of%20completion.%20One%20said%20I%20likely%20had%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fhealth%2Fmental-health%2Ftypes-of-ocd%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emild%20form%20of%20OCD%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20another%20considered%20it%20a%20childish%20habit%20I%20would%20eventually%20grow%20out%20of%20(I'm%2036)%2C%20and%20the%20last%20agreed%20that%20it%20was%20likely%20OCD%20mixed%20with%20ADHD%20mixed%20with%20anxiety%20and%20was%20likely%20an%20acquired%20form%20of%20self-soothing%20in%20a%20world%20that%20is%20unpredictable%2C%20uncertain%2C%20and%20possibly%20doomed.%20Yes%2C%20she%20agreed%20with%20me%20that%20the%20world%20was%20possibly%20doomed.%20This%20is%20how%20I%20knew%20she%20was%20the%20therapist%20for%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHow%20do%20you%20choose%20what%20to%20read%20next%3F%26quot%3B%20she%20asked.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20just%20go%20down%20the%20list.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOkay%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BWhat%20would%20happen%20if%20you%20just%20threw%20away%20the%20list%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOh%2C%26quot%3B%20I%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20can't%20do%20that.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20couldn't%20do%20that%20because%20if%20I%20threw%20away%20the%20book%20list%2C%20I%20would%20have%20to%20make%20a%20conscious%20choice.%20Making%20a%20conscious%20choice%20would%20require%20being%20confronted%20by%20the%20reality%20of%20life.%20And%20the%20current%20reality%20of%20life%20was%20terrifying%20and%20full%20of%20things%20I%20couldn't%20control%2C%20and%20more%20questions%20I%20didn't%20want%20to%20consider%20%E2%80%94%20did%20I%20want%20to%20have%20children%3F%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fboreout-tiktok-workplace-phenomenon-opposite-burnout-still-harmful-workers-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EDid%20I%20like%20my%20work%3C%2Fa%3E%3F%20Was%20I%20actually%20satisfied%20with%20the%20shape%20of%20my%20days%3F%20I'd%20spent%20the%20last%2010%20years%20reading%2C%20but%20did%20I%20actually%20remember%20what%20I'd%20read%3F%20In%20most%20instances%2C%20no.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20turned%2036%20this%20year.%20I've%20come%20to%20an%20unsettling%20conclusion%20that%20I%20might%20now%20be%20in%20the%20back%20half%20of%20my%20life%2C%20and%20I%2C%20terrifyingly%2C%20don't%20remember%20the%20majority%20of%20what%20I've%20read%20because%20the%20point%20wasn't%20in%20the%20experience%2C%20the%20point%20was%20in%20the%20completion.%20Two%20years%20ago%2C%20I%20successfully%20swore%20off%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fhealth%2Fmental-health%2Fdoomscrolling%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esocial%20media%20doomscrolling%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20was%20so%20darn%20proud%20of%20myself%20for%20it.%20Turns%20out%2C%20I%20transferred%20all%20that%20doomscrolling%20into%20my%20creative%20life%2C%20dissociating%20now%20with%20my%20books.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhen%20I%20lost%20my%20book%20list%2C%20I%20actually%20felt%20free%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ETwo%20months%20ago%2C%20I%20reorganized%20my%20cloud%20account%20where%20the%20list%20was%20kept.%20I%20don't%20know%20what%20happened%2C%20but%20the%20list%20got%20lost%20in%20the%20shuffle.%20I%20tried%20to%20restore%20it%2C%20searched%20all%20the%20trash%20cans%2C%20hit%20the%20undo%20button%20%E2%80%94%20but%20it%20was%20gone.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStrangely%2C%20I%20did%20not%20panic%20like%20I%20thought%20I%20would.%20Ever%20since%20my%20therapist%20had%20introduced%20the%20idea%20of%20throwing%20the%20list%20away%2C%20I%20had%20fantasized%20about%20the%20moment%20but%20never%20actually%20committed%20to%20it.%20Now%2C%20regardless%20of%20how%20it%20had%20happened%2C%20the%20moment%20was%20here.%20The%20list%20was%20dead.%20And%20with%20it%2C%20I%20was%20free.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20testament%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcan-i-go-to-therapy-if-im-not-depressed-2017-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emy%20therapist's%20prowess%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20I%20paused.%20I%20didn't%20read%20anything%20for%20several%20days.%20Finally%2C%20I%20went%20to%20a%20bookstore.%20I%20browsed%20the%20aisles%20and%20let%20myself%20be%20drawn%20in%20by%20the%20covers.%20I%20picked%20up%20one%20title%20that%20looked%20interesting%2C%20and%20I%20allowed%20myself%20to%20buy%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20loss%20of%20the%20book%20list%20proved%20to%20be%20a%20harbinger%20of%20things%20to%20come%3B%20I%20returned%20all%20the%20overdue%20books%20stacked%20on%20my%20nightstand%20back%20to%20the%20library%20without%20reading%20them%20first%2C%20leaving%20a%20clean%2C%20clear%20space%20of%20open%20opportunity.%20Quieter%20and%20quieter%20my%20days%20became%20until%20there%20I%20was%20%E2%80%94%20my%20own%20voice%20in%20my%20own%20head%20once%20again%2C%20in%20all%20her%20anxiety.%20I%20liked%20her.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20will%20always%20be%20a%20completist.%20Know%20thyself%2C%20as%20they%20say.%20Thus%2C%20I%20declare%20this%20the%20year%20of%20re-reading%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-read-books-goal-app-new-years-resolution-2023-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebooks%20I've%20loved%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20past%20without%20worrying%20that%20I'm%20not%20spending%20my%20time%20reading%20something%20new.%20I%20will%20roam%20bookshelves%20again%20and%20stumble%20upon%20something%20that%20looks%20amazing%20and%20devour%20it%20because%20I%20want%3Cem%3E%20%3C%2Fem%3Eto%2C%20not%20because%20I%20have%20to.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20I%2C%20along%20with%20many%20others%2C%20am%20saying%20goodbye%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewalrus.ca%2Fgoodreads-is-terrible%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etoxicity%20of%20Goodreads%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftiktok-changes-book-publishing-marketing-author-careers-2023-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eperformance%20of%20Booktok%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20the%20competitive%20urge%20to%20read%20quantitatively%2C%20rather%20than%20creatively.%20Books%20and%20stories%20are%20not%20simply%20content%20to%20be%20binged%20like%20a%20bad%20meal.%20They%20are%20our%20art.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhat%20thoughts%20might%20bubble%20up%20given%20the%20space%20to%20make%20decisions%20in%20the%20moment%3F%20What%20inspiration%20will%20find%20its%20way%20into%20my%20clear%20and%20open%20mind%3F%20Maybe%20I'll%20make%20a%20list.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Freading-list-books-to-read-ocd-2024-2%5C%22%3EBusiness%