20for%20the%20Higher%20Judicial%20Service%2C%20and%20a%20few%20years%20later%20elevated%20to%20the%20Bench.%20However%2C%20somewhere%20in%20the%20back%20of%20my%20mind%2C%20the%20epithet%20%E2%80%9CBench%20fixing%E2%80%9D%20kept%20haunting.%20And%2C%20to%20my%20surprise%20and%20dismay%2C%20I%20realized%20that%20though%20in%20the%20High%20Court%2C%20the%20Registry%E2%80%99s%20hands%20were%20clipped%20by%20the%20Roster%20System%2C%20that%20system%20too%20was%20not%20free%20from%20rat%E2%80%99s%20smell.%20And%20that%20smell%20emanated%20principally%20from%20the%20pen%20of%20the%20Chief%20Justice%20who%20was%20incharge%20of%20the%20Roster.%20None%20of%20the%20so-called%20Service%20Judges%20was%20ever%20assigned%20important%20constitutional%20matters%2C%20habeas%20corpus%20or%20other%20writ%20petitions%20involving%20important%20questions%20of%20law.%20All%20such%20cases%20went%20to%20judges%20directly%20elevated%20from%20the%20Bar.%20As%20if%2C%20the%20judges%20from%20the%20Bar%20were%20paragon%20of%20knowledge.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20Narasimha%20Rao%E2%80%99s%20bribery%20case%20which%20revolved%20around%20the%20interpretation%20of%20Article%20105%20of%20the%20Constitution%2C%20and%20involving%20not%20only%20the%20person%20who%20held%20the%20position%20of%20the%20Prime%20Minister%2C%20but%20other%20equally%20important%20persons%2C%20showed%20not%20only%20the%20judge%E2%80%99s%20indefatigable%20courage%2C%20but%20also%20his%20complete%20grasp%20over%20the%20Constitution%20of%20India%2C%20and%20its%20interpretation.%20But%2C%20what%20is%20important%20in%20the%20present%20context%20is%20that%20the%20author%20of%20the%20judgement%20was%20a%20service%20judge.%20Make%20no%20mistake%2C%20the%20case%20was%20not%20assigned%20to%20him.%20It%20landed%20before%20him%20because%20he%20happened%20to%20be%20sitting%20in%20a%20criminal%20roster%2C%20and%20the%20question%20with%20regard%20to%20the%20interpretation%20of%20Article%20105%20of%20the%20Constitution%20arose%20out%20of%20that%20case.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnd%2C%20what%20is%20the%20present%20state%20of%20affairs%2C%20particularly%20in%20Supreme%20Court.%20It%20has%20taken%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20more%20than%20five%20years%20to%20decide%20Electrol%20Bond%20petitions%20involving%20the%20very%20existence%2C%20and%20fairness%20of%20the%20electrol%20process.%20Chief%20Justices%20came%20and%20Chief%20Justices%20went%20away%2C%20each%20shying%20away%20from%20taking%20up%20the%20issue%20head%20on.%20To%20be%20fair%20to%20the%20then%20Chief%20Justice%20of%20India%2C%20even%20in%20the%20height%20of%20emergency%2C%20when%20Smt.%20Indra%20Gandhi%20reigned%20Supreme%2C%20he%20did%20not%20shy%20away%20from%20constituting%20a%20Bench%20and%20taking%20up%20the%20matter%20of%20%3Cem%3EADM%20Jabalpur%3C%2Fem%3E.%20It%20is%20a%20different%20matter%20that%20its%20outcome%20was%20highly%20damning%20to%20the%20fundamental%20rights%20of%20the%20citizen%2C%20and%20it%20remains%20an%20ugly%20spot%20on%20the%20fair%20face%20of%20the%20judiciary.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhy%20no%20urgency%20was%20felt%20or%20realised%20by%20one%20Chief%20Justice%20after%20another%20in%20the%20Electoral%20Bonds%20cases%20or%20others%20similar%20matters%20involving%20the%20rights%20of%20the%20citizens%3F%20In%20the%20interregnum%2C%20much%20water%20has%20already%20flown%20under%20the%20bridge.%20One%20general%20election%2C%20and%20many%20elections%20to%20the%20State%20Legislatures%2C%20had%20taken%20place%20in%20the%20meanwhile.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnd%2C%20imagine%2C%20when%20a%20judgement%20like%20in%20the%20Electoral%20Bonds%20matter%20comes%20protecting%20the%20rights%20of%20the%20citizens%2C%20they%20are%20not%20only%20pleasantly%20surprised%2C%20but%20feel%20so%20relieved%20as%20to%20hail%20and%20thank%20the%20Supreme%20Court%2C%20even%20when%20it%20has%20only%20performed%20its%20constitutional%20duty.%20And%20when%20it%20does%20that%2C%20it%20neither%20needs%20applause%20nor%20brickbats.%20But%20the%20fact%20that%20such%20was%20the%20reaction%20shows%20how%20much%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20has%20lost%20in%20terms%20of%20credibility%20in%20the%20field%20of%20justice%20delivery%20system.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Supreme%20Court%20is%20no%20longer%20taken%20as%20the%20last%20word%20on%20any%20such%20pronouncement.%20It%20is%20already%20being%20said%20that%20the%20government%20may%20move%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20for%20review%2C%20or%20the%20State%20Bank%20of%20India%20and%20the%20Election%20Commission%20may%20ask%20for%20further%20time%20to%20carry%20out%20its%20directions%2C%20or%20the%20government%20may%20even%20bring%20an%20Ordinance%20to%20nullify%20the%20effect%20of%20the%20judgement.%20After%20all%2C%20the%20government%20did%20bring%20an%20Ordinance%20to%20reverse%20the%20judgement%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20in%20the%20matter%20of%20selection%20of%20the%20Election%20Commissioners%20by%20removing%20the%20Chief%20Justice%20of%20India%20as%20being%20part%20of%20such%20selection.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhy%20have%20things%20come%20to%20such%20a%20pass%3F%20The%20government%20is%20not%20entirely%20to%20be%20blamed.%20Somewhere%20down%20the%20line%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20allowed%20its%20authority%20to%20dilute.%20Though%20it%20is%20unfortunate%2C%20keeping%20in%20view%20the%20past%20performance%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%2C%20one%20feels%2C%20it%20is%20the%20government%20which%20will%20have%20the%20last%20laugh.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELet%20me%20take%20you%20to%20the%20past.%20The%20aggrieved%20citizen%20was%20known%20by%20the%20name%20of%20Maneka%20Gandhi.%20Our%20Supreme%20Court%20said%2C%20and%20I%20quote%2C%20that%20%E2%80%9Cspeedy%20trial%20is%20a%20dynamic%20and%20progressive%20program%20of%20legal%20assistance%2C%20an%20essential%20ingredient%20of%20the%20right%20to%20life%20and%20liberty%20and%20flows%20directly%20from%20Article%2021%20of%20the%20Constitution%E2%80%9D.%20Brave%20words%2C%20but%20lost%20somewhere%20in%20the%20wilderness%20of%20the%20Roster%20regime.%20You%20do%20not%20live%20on%20words%20alone.%20They%20need%20a%20heart.%20And%20a%20heart%20that%20flutters.%20Thousands%20and%20thousands%20are%20rotting%20in%20jails%2C%20standing%20in%20the%20corridors%20of%20courts%20of%20justice%2C%20day%20in%20and%20day%20out%2C%20with%20prayers%20on%20their%20lips%2C%20hoping%20for%20the%20rule%2C%20%E2%80%9CBail%20not%20Jail%E2%80%9Dto%20resurrect.%20But%20it%20surfaces%20only%20for%20the%20chosen%20few.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESiddique%20Kappan%2C%20a%20journalist%20who%20was%20arrested%20on%20October%205%2C%202020%2C%20got%20bail%20after%20more%20than%20two%20years.%20When%20he%20approached%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20under%20Article%2032%20of%20the%20Constitution%2C%20the%20then%20Chief%20Justice%20of%20India%20remarked%20that%20we%20want%20to%20discourage%20Article%2032%20petitions%2C%20and%20he%20was%20sent%20back%20to%20the%20High%20Court.%20More%20recently%2C%20Supreme%20Court%20declined%20to%20hear%20an%20Article%2032%20petition%20involving%20the%20arrest%20of%20Chief%20Minister%20of%20a%20State%20who%20alleged%20that%20he%20was%20arrested%20on%20no%20evidence%2C%20and%20with%20the%20sole%20aim%20of%20destabilising%20his%20duly%20elected%20government.%20The%20Bench%20observed%2C%20%E2%80%9Cwhy%20have%20you%20come%20here%20directly%E2%80%9D.%20This%20observation%20was%20made%20notwithstanding%20the%20fact%20that%20many%20a%20times%20in%20the%20past%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20has%20been%20entertaining%20Article%2032%20petitions%20depending%20upon%20the%20urgency%20and%20gravity%20of%20the%20matter.%20And%2C%20more%20importantly%2C%20the%20observation%20has%20come%20notwithstanding%20the%20golden%20words%20of%20B.R.%20Ambedkar%2C%20the%20architect%20of%20the%20Constitution%2C%20describing%20Article%2032%20as%20the%20%E2%80%9Cheart%20and%20soul%20of%20the%20Constitution%E2%80%9D.%20Is%20Article%2032%20to%20be%20treated%20as%20a%20dead%20letter%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERemember%20the%20landmark%20judgement%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findiankanoon.org%2Fdoc%2F1373215%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EHussanara%20Khatoon%20vs.%20State%20of%20Bihar%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3F%20Recollect%20what%20the%20judges%20said%3F%20Let%20me%20remind%20you.%20They%20not%20only%20felt%20that%20there%20was%20a%20shocking%20state%20of%20affairs%20so%20far%20as%20the%20administration%20of%20law%20and%20order%20is%20concerned%2C%20but%20also%20that%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20legal%20system%20has%20lost%20its%20credibility%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EArun%20Shourie%20has%20beautifully%20described%20the%20present%20state%20of%20judiciary%20in%20his%20remarkably%20readable%20book%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Commission%20for%20Lost%20Causes%3C%2Fem%3E.%20He%20calls%20the%20judges%20as%20%E2%80%9CLions%20under%20the%20throne%E2%80%9D.%20The%20misfortune%20is%20that%20many%20of%20them%20have%20not%20only%20lost%20their%20teeth%20but%20roar%20too%2C%20leaving%20the%20ordinary%20citizen%20to%20the%20mercy%20of%20predators%20and%20jackals.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhat%20we%20find%20today%20is%20that%20while%20a%20powerful%20person%20gets%20bail%20on%20an%20experimental%20basis%2C%20men%20like%20Umar%20Khalid%20are%20withering%20away%2C%20unwept%2C%20unsung%20and%20unheard%2C%20and%20so%20fed%20up%20that%20coming%20out%20of%20the%20corridors%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20is%20itself%20considered%20a%20relief.%20While%20a%20journalist%20spends%20time%20in%20jail%20for%20the%20mere%20crime%20of%20performing%20his%20duty%2C%20an%20old%20and%20ailing%20man%20unable%20to%20even%20sip%20water%20is%20denied%20basic%20medical%20aid%2C%20and%20is%20made%20to%20suffer%20and%20die%20behind%20the%20bars.%20What%20has%20happened%20to%20Article%2021%3F%20Why%20have%20those%20swearing%20by%20the%20Constitution%20forgotten%20cases%20like%20Hussainara%2C%20M.H.%20Hoskot%2C%20Sunil%20Batra%20and%20A.K.%20Roy%3F%20What%20has%20happened%20to%20those%20brave%20words%20in%3Cem%3E%20Rattan%20Singh%20versus%20State%20of%20Punja%3C%2Fem%3Eb%20(AIR%201982%20Supreme%20Court%201)%2C%20%E2%80%9C%E2%80%A6If%20freedom%20and%20liberty%20are%20to%20have%20any%20meaning%20in%20our%20democratic%20setup%2C%20it%20is%20essential%20that%20at%20least%20those%20safeguards%20are%20not%20denied.%E2%80%9D%20Is%20our%20judiciary%20pushing%20down%20who%20deserve%20to%20be%20pushed%20down%20and%20pulling%20up%20who%20deserve%20to%20be%20pulled%20up%2C%20or%20is%20it%20just%20becoming%20gilded%20tomb%20of%20a%20failed%20talent%3F%20The%20question%20is%20not%20who%20is%20making%20them%20dance.%20The%20question%20is%20who%20is%20dancing%20and%20why%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20I%20was%20penning%20these%20lines%2C%20I%20had%20before%20me%20two%20headlines%20in%20the%20%3Cem%3EIndian%20Express%3C%2Fem%3E.%20Without%20a%20comment%2C%20I%20am%20reading%20them%20out%20to%20you%2C%20leaving%20it%20to%20you%20to%20react.%20Here%20is%20the%20first%20one.%20A%20Bench%20of%20Justice%20B.R.%20Gavai%20and%20Sandeep%20Mehta%20observed%20%E2%80%9Cwhen%20the%20question%20of%20liberty%20of%20a%20person%20is%20involved%2C%20even%20a%C2%A0day%E2%80%99s%20delay%20counts%E2%80%9D%20(January%2018%2C%202024)%20and%20here%20is%20the%20second%20one%2C%20%E2%80%9C24%20years%20after%20a%20man%20dies%20in%20police%20custody%2C%20ex-cop%20sentenced%20to%2010%20years%20jail%E2%80%9D.%20How%20do%20you%20reconcile%20the%20two%3F%20One%20decries%20even%20a%20day%E2%80%99s%20delay%20and%20the%20other%20tells%20us%20of%20delay%20of%2024%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERemember%20those%20five%20judges%20of%20the%20press%20conference%20fame.%20One%20of%20them%2C%20a%20friend%20from%20days%20of%20our%20mutual%20struggle%20at%20the%20Bar%2C%20is%20present%20today.%20What%20happened%20thereafter%3F%20Any%20reform%3F%20Any%20improvement%3F%20Let%20us%20remember%20that%20a%20driver%E2%80%99s%20competence%20is%20not%20established%20by%20his%20dress%20or%20his%20religious%20fervor%20made%20public%2C%20but%20by%20making%20his%20passengers%20reach%20their%20destination%20safely.%20A%20judge%20must%20fall%20in%20love%20with%20the%20Constitution%20before%20he%20approaches%20it.%20The%20original%20is%20beautiful.%20Its%20reach%20is%20not%20limited.%20It%20is%20not%20the%20Roster%2C%20it%20is%20the%20judge%20who%20assigns%20the%20cases%2C%20and%20it%20is%20the%20judge%20who%20decides%20the%20matter.%3Cbr%3E%5CnShakespeare%20in%20Julius%20Caesar%20writes%3A%20%E2%80%9CHis%20life%20was%20gentle%2C%20and%20the%20elements%20so%20mixed%20in%20him%20that%20Nature%20might%20stand-up.%20And%20say%20to%20all%20the%20world.%20This%20was%20a%20man.%E2%80%9D%20Are%20we%20today%20too%20sure%20of%20the%20presence%20of%20such%20a%20man%3F%20If%20not%2C%20surely%2C%20we%20need%20him%2C%20though%20many%20today%20are%20seen%20taking%20a%20deep%20breath%20and%20agreeing%20with%20Meer%20Taqi%20Meer%3A%20%E2%80%9C%3Cem%3EIbtadaai%20ishq%20hai%2C%20rota%20hai%20kya%20agey%20agey%20dekhiye%20hota%20hai%20kya.%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20having%20said%20all%20this%2C%20I%20will%20be%20unfair%20to%20the%20Roster%20System%2C%20and%20to%20its%20Master%2C%20by%20not%20pointing%20out%20at%20least%20three%20pronounced%20advantages%20of%20the%20Roster%20System%20and%20which%2C%20fortunately%20or%20unfortunately%2C%20have%20already%20become%20public%20and%2C%20they%20are%20as%20follows%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E1.%20The%20Master%20of%20Roster%20can%20constitute%20a%20Bench%20of%20his%20own%20choice%20and%20himself%20preside%20over%20it%20even%20in%20a%20very%20personal%20matter.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E2.%20By%20intelligently%20making%20use%20of%20that%20power%2C%20he%20can%20assure%20himself%2C%20even%20after%20his%20retirement%2C%20a%20cozy%20job%20like%20a%20seat%20in%20the%20Rajya%20Sabha%20or%20Governorship%20in%20some%20state.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E3.%20By%20intelligently%20using%20that%20power%2C%20he%20can%20equally%20benefit%20his%20very%20worthy%20and%20dearest%20colleagues%20too.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThank%20you%20very%20much.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A170886392