t%20states%20cannot%20unilaterally%20leave%2C%20holding%20that%20the%20US%20is%20%26quot%3Ban%20indestructible%20union.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMiller%20called%20the%20SCOTUS%20ruling%20%26quot%3Bone%20of%20the%20biggest%20jokes%20known%20to%20man.%26quot%3B%20He%20cited%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.senate.gov%2Fabout%2Forigins-foundations%2Fsenate-and-constitution%2Fconstitution.htm%23a1_sec10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EArticle%201%20Section%2010%20of%20the%20US%20Constitution%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20lists%20things%20states%20are%20not%20allowed%20to%20do%2C%20like%20mint%20their%20own%20currency%20or%20sign%20treaties.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20noted%20that%20it%20doesn't%20say%20states%20can't%20leave.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20fantasy%20with%20unlikely%20allies%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EJames%20Henson%2C%20the%20director%20of%20the%20Texas%20Politics%20Project%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Texas%20at%20Austin%2C%20told%20BI%20that%20while%20the%20independence%20movement%20may%20be%20loud%2C%20it%20is%20unrealistic%20and%20has%20little%20support%20among%20Texans.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFor%20the%20most%20part%2C%20this%20is%20a%20fantasy%20projection%20among%20a%20very%20small%20sliver%20of%20people%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20I%20think%20the%20romance%20of%20some%20general%20notion%20of%20Texas%20independence%20wears%20off%20pretty%20fast%20if%20people%20were%20to%20start%20considering%20it%20seriously.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20pointed%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftexaspolitics.utexas.edu%2Fset%2Fdo-you-consider-yourself-be-american-first-or-texan-first-february-2024%23overall%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ea%20recent%20poll%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%201%2C300%20Texans%20by%20his%20project%2C%20which%20found%20that%2063%25%20of%20responding%20Texans%20consider%20themselves%20Americans%20first%20and%20Texans%20second%2C%20compared%20with%20the%2026%25%20who%20put%20Texas%20first.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe