22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22China's%20master%20plan%20to%20crush%20Elon%20Musk%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Elon%20Musk%20sitting%20on%20a%20red%20Tesla%2C%20with%20a%20business%20shoe%20and%20red%20pant%20leg%20adorned%20with%20yellow%20stars%20in%20the%20foreground%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65d8ec4790413ab8e1d6811b%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22600%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EChina's%20EV%20ascendance%20has%20sparked%20a%20fight%20that%20is%20forcing%20American%20companies%20to%20rethink%20their%20whole%20strategy.%3Cp%3EGetty%20Images%3B%20Alyssa%20Powell%2FInsider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20Tesla%20CEO%20Elon%20Musk%20was%20asked%20in%202011%20about%20the%20Chinese%20electric-car%20maker%20BYD%20%E2%80%94%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fnews%2Fstocks%2Fbyd-stock-sales-warren-buffett-berkshire-hathaway-china-ev-munger-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EWarren%20Buffett-backed%3C%2Fa%3E%20company%20focused%20on%20cheaper%20eclectic%20vehicles%20with%20a%20name%20short%20for%20Build%20Your%20Dreams%20%E2%80%94%20he%20simply%20laughed%20it%20off.%20%26quot%3BHave%20you%20seen%20their%20car%3F%26quot%3B%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bloomberg.com%2Fnews%2Fvideos%2F2023-12-27%2Fin-2011-tesla-ceo-musk-mocked-chinese-competitor-byd-video%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehe%20said%20with%20a%20giggle%20to%20Bloomberg%20TV%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20adding%20that%20BYD%20didn't%20%26quot%3Bhave%20a%20great%20product%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3Bthe%20technology%20is%20not%20very%20strong.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMusk's%20juvenile%20expression%20of%20hubris%20was%20(and%20still%20is)%20singular%2C%20but%20his%20belief%20that%20China's%20automakers%20were%20not%20a%20threat%20was%20shared%20across%20the%20US%20auto%20industry%20at%20the%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20lot%20can%20change%20in%2013%20years.%20BYD%20eclipsed%20Tesla%20in%202023%20as%20the%20best-selling%20EV%20maker%20in%20the%20world.%20One%20out%20of%20every%20three%20electric%20cars%20sold%20is%20made%20by%20the%20company%2C%20up%20from%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bloomberg.com%2Fnews%2Ffeatures%2F2023-06-26%2Fchina-s-electric-vehicle-bubble-is-starting-to-deflate%3Fembedded-checkout%3Dtrue%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E15%25%20in%202020%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInstead%20of%20laughing%20off%20the%20competition%2C%20Musk%20is%20now%20sounding%20the%20alarm%20on%20threats%20from%20Chinese%20automakers.%20On%20a%20conference%20call%20with%20investors%20in%20January%2C%20he%20said%20Chinese%20EVs%20would%20%26quot%3Bpretty%20much%20demolish%26quot%3B%20other%20American%20carmakers%20if%20allowed%20to%20enter%20the%20US.%20America's%20biggest%20car%20companies%20have%20also%20started%20to%20recognize%20that%20they%20must%20figure%20out%20how%20to%20make%20electric%20cars%20cheap%20as%20soon%20as%20possible%20before%20China%20eats%20their%20lunch.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20likes%20of%20Tesla%2C%20GM%2C%20and%20Ford%20are%20rolling%20out%20a%20handful%20of%20high-priced%20luxury%20EV%20models%2C%20Chinese%20companies%20already%20offer%20a%20slew%20of%20options%20across%20a%20range%20of%20price%20points%3A%20starter%20EVs%2C%20beater%20EVs%2C%20ones%20for%20getting%20from%20point%20A%20to%20point%20B.%20And%20while%20the%20American%20automakers%20are%20still%20trying%20to%20win%20over%20consumers%20just%20in%20their%20own%20country%2C%20Beijing%20is%20already%20planning%20to%20work%20around%20trade%20barriers%20and%20get%20these%20cars%20sold%20around%20the%20world%2C%20including%20in%20the%20US.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20thought%20that%20Chinese-quality%20engineering%20and%20design%20are%20not%20as%20high%20quality%20as%20the%20legacy%20carmakers%20%E2%80%94%20that%20should%20be%20put%20to%20bed%2C%26quot%3B%20Tu%20Le%2C%20the%20founder%20of%20Sino%20Auto%20Insights%2C%20a%20consultancy%20focusing%20on%20the%20Chinese%20EV%20market%2C%20told%20me.%20%26quot%3BRight%20now%2C%20the%20legacies%20don't%20have%20competitive%20products.%20There's%20a%20vacuum.%20If%20China%20EV%20Inc.%20were%20allowed%20to%20enter%20the%20US%20today%20or%20next%20year%2C%20the%20legacies%20would%20be%20gutted.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20are%20witnessing%20a%20shock%20to%20the%20global%20automotive%20order%20unseen%20since%20Japan%20barreled%20into%20the%20market%20in%20the%201970s.%20China's%20EV%20ascendance%20has%20sparked%20a%20fight%20that%20is%20forcing%20companies%20to%20stretch%20the%20limits%20of%20their%20technological%20capability%20and%20policymakers%20to%20reimagine%20the%20ideological%20underpinnings%20of%20decades%20of%20trade%20strategy.%20What's%20at%20stake%20is%20nothing%20less%20than%20a%20US%20industry%20worth%20%24104%20billion%2C%20about%20as%20much%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.trade.gov%2Fcountry-commercial-guides%2Fangola-market-overview%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAngola%3C%2Fa%3E's%20national%20GDP%2C%20and%20all%20the%203%20million%20jobs%20that%20come%20with%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20a%20global%20game.%20It%20has%20been%20a%20global%20game%2C%26quot%3B%20Le%20said.%20%26quot%3BMotherfuckers%20just%20haven't%20been%20paying%20attention.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20safe%20to%20say%20EVs%20have%20moved%20beyond%20the%20%26quot%3Bearly%20adopter%26quot%3B%20phase%20of%20the%20technological%20life%20cycle%20and%20are%20now%20working%20to%20conquer%20mainstream%20car%20buyers%20in%20the%20US.%20In%202023%2C%201%20million%20were%20sold%20in%20the%20country%20for%20the%20first%20time%2C%20up%20from%20918%2C500%20in%202022.%20Despite%20this%20growth%2C%20there%20have%20been%20flashing%20red%20signs%20that%20American%20automakers'%20strategy%20%E2%80%94%20making%20EVs%20that%20are%20just%20like%20combustion-engine%20cars%20but%20about%20%2410%2C000%20more%20expensive%20%E2%80%94%20isn't%20working.%20Projections%20for%20sales%20growth%20in%20the%20years%20ahead%20have%20come%20down%2C%20and%20consumers%20have%20expressed%20dissatisfaction%20with%20the%20crop%20of%20cars%20available.%20To%20overcome%20that%2C%20carmakers%20have%20realized%20they%20must%20lure%20customers%20with%20cheaper%20models.%20Earlier%20this%20month%2C%20Ford%20CEO%20Jim%20Farley%20said%20his%20company%20was%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fford-tesla-model-2-elon-musk-jim-farley-electric-vehicles-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eruthlessly%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%20focused%20on%20developing%20a%20more%20affordable%20mass-market%20car.%20Tesla%20has%20been%20saying%20a%20cheaper%20car%20is%20on%20the%20way%20for%20years%2C%20without%20success%20(%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftesla-elon-musk-to-build-affordable-electric-car-report-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eyet%3C%2Fa%3E).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20US%20carmakers%20are%20still%20figuring%20out%20how%20to%20please%20a%20wide%20variety%20of%20customers%2C%20Chinese%20brands%20have%20EVs%20in%20about%20every%20form%20imaginable.%20Want%20a%20%2410%2C000%20car%3F%20Try%20the%20BYD%20Seagull.%20Want%20a%20luxury%20SUV%20that%20can%20float%20in%20water%3F%20That's%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Frobbreport.com%2Fmotors%2Fcars%2Fbyd-yangwang-u8-suv-waterproof-boat-mode-1235029369%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBYD%20U8%20Premium%20Edition%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Want%20something%20more%20luxurious%3F%20Chery%2C%20another%20Chinese%20carmaker%2C%20launched%20a%20sexy%20EV%20sports%20car%20with%20scissor%20doors%20called%20the%20iCar%2C%20which%20costs%20between%20%2421%2C800%20and%20%2458%2C000.%20China's%20ability%20to%20expand%20its%20suite%20of%20offerings%20comes%20down%20to%20cost.%20Of%20course%2C%20the%20US%20has%20higher%20labor%20costs%2C%20but%20China%20has%20also%20taken%20great%20pains%20to%20own%20the%20EV%20supply%20chain.%20Legacy%20carmakers%20are%20still%20searching%20around%20the%20world%20to%20source%20the%20raw%20materials%20and%20parts%20they%20need%2C%20a%20project%20the%20Chinese%20government%20has%20been%20working%20on%20for%20over%20a%20decade.%20In%20fact%2C%20many%20of%20these%20companies%20are%20selling%20their%20products%20to%20American%20firms%3A%20Tesla%20buys%20batteries%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cnn.com%2F2022%2F06%2F08%2Ftech%2Fbyd-tesla-ev-batteries-intl-hnk%2Findex.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efrom%20BYD%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20for%20example.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20doesn't%20mean%20Chinese%20car%20companies%20aren't%20facing%20challenges.%20While%20the%20US's%20strategy%20(or%20lack%20thereof)%20has%20left%20us%20without%20enough%20chargers%20or%20the%20right%20kind%20of%20inventory%2C%20China%20has%20the%20opposite%20problem.%20It%20has%20too%20many%20EVs%2C%20too%20many%20EV%20makers%2C%20and%20a%20flagging%20domestic%20economy.%20China%20EV%20Inc.%20needs%20to%20expand%20to%20new%20markets.%20The%20future%20of%20the%20auto%20industry%20hangs%20on%20whether%20it%20can%20start%20to%20do%20that%20before%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20world%20can%20catch%20up.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20year%20Musk%20tittered%20at%20the%20idea%20of%20Chinese%20EVs%20overtaking%20Tesla%2C%20the%20country%20produced%20only%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmacropolo.org%2Fanalysis%2Fchina-electric-vehicle-ev-industry%2F%23%3A~%3Atext%3DIn%2520December%25202019%252C%2520the%2520Chinese%2Coverall%2520vehicle%2520sales%2520by%25202025%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E5%2C000%20electric%20cars%3C%2Fa%3E.%20But%20Beijing's%20plan%20to%20dominate%20the%20global%20EV%20space%20was%20already%20well%20underway.%20The%20Chinese%20Communist%20Party%20started%20out%20by%20setting%20the%20goal%20of%20having%20EVs%20make%20up%2025%25%20of%20all%20cars%20sold%20in%20China%20by%202025%20and%20showered%20money%20on%20companies%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheicct.org%2Fsubsidy-fraud-leads-to-reforms-for-chinas-ev-market%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eanything%20even%20resembling%20a%20plan%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20contribute%20to%20that%20goal.%20At%20the%20same%20time%2C%20the%20government%20set%20about%20marshaling%20all%20the%20raw%20materials%20Chinese%20companies%20would%20need%20for%20EV%20batteries%20and%20drivetrains%2C%20creating%20a%20domestic%20ecosystem%20for%20suppliers.%20In%20this%20way%2C%20its%20industrial%20policy%20for%20EVs%20copied%20past%20plans%20to%20dominate%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fgmk.center%2Fen%2Fposts%2Fchinas-overcapacity-problem-returns%2F%23%3A~%3Atext%3DThroughout%2520most%2520of%25202023%252C%2520Chinese%2Cexcess%2520steelmaking%2520capacity%2520in%2520China.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esteel%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fprosperousamerica.org%2Fis-china-overproducing-solar-again-iea-report-says-yes%2F%23%3A~%3Atext%3DChina%2520accounts%2520for%2520almost%252090%2Cenergy%2520forecast%2520report%2520this%2520month.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esolar%20panels%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20flood%20the%20market%20with%20supply%20until%20Chinese%20manufacturers%20were%20the%20only%20game%20in%20town.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20in%202016%2C%20the%20CCP%20changed%20course.%20The%20grant%20money%20for%20EV%20research%20and%20development%20petered%20out%2C%20and%20the%20government%20announced%20that%20by%202027%2C%20it%20would%20phase%20out%20subsidies%20that%20lowered%20the%20price%20of%20electric%20cars%20for%20consumers.%20Beijing%20also%20instituted%20policies%20that%20opened%20the%20door%20for%20foreign%20carmakers%20to%20invest%20more%20in%20China's%20domestic%20industry%20and%20move%20manufacturing%20there.%20The%20result%20was%20pure%20carnage%20for%20China's%20domestic%20EV%20industry.%20Companies%20that%20depended%20on%20Beijing%20for%20subsidies%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftechcrunch.com%2F2023%2F10%2F10%2Fwm-motors-bankruptcy-highlights-challenges-faced-by-ev-startups-in-china%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebegan%20to%20implode%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20small%20players%20got%20pushed%20out%20of%20the%20market.%20But%20the%20chaos%20ended%20up%20strengthening%20the%20country's%20auto%20sector%2C%20ensuring%20that%20the%20most%20competitive%20carmakers%20gained%20market%20share.%20What%20emerged%20started%20to%20look%20more%20like%20a%20more%20mature%20industry%20%E2%80%94%20one%20with%20the%20capacity%20to%20manufacture%20world-class%20products.%20Last%20year%2C%20China%20became%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Fworld%2Fchina%2Fchina-vehicle-sales-rise-further-boosted-by-stimulus-policies-sales-promotions-3452cca1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eworld's%20largest%20auto%20exporter%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Chinese%20President%20Xi%20Jinping%20makes%20a%20toast%20after%20delivering%20his%20speech%20at%20a%20dinner%20marking%20the%2074th%20anniversary%20of%20the%20founding%20of%20the%20People's%20Republic%20of%20China%20at%20the%20Great%20Hall%20of%20the%20People%20on%20September%2028%2C%202023%20in%20Beijing%2C%20China.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65c46d1f43bb77284ba4cfcd%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223333%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EXi%20Jinping's%20goal%20is%20to%20make%20China%20the%20world's%20leading%20manufacturer%20of%20electric%20cars%20%E2%80%94%20no%20matter%20what%20it%20takes.%3Cp%3EAndy%20Wong-Pool%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ENone%20of%20this%20means%20the%20road%20ahead%20is%20any%20easier%20for%20the%20victors%20of%20Beijing's%20EV%20wars.%20Chinese%20automakers%20now%20have%20to%20deal%20with%20slower%20domestic%20demand%20as%20the%20Chinese%20economy%20enters%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchina-economy-shrinking-xi-jinping-debt-real-estate-american-world-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eprotracted%20phase%20of%20slower%20growth%3C%2Fa%3E.%20At%20the%20same%20time%2C%20they%20know%20that%20their%20growth%20and%20success%20are%20central%20to%20the%20vision%20of%20China's%20technological%20landscape%20that%20its%20leader%2C%20Xi%20Jinping%2C%20has.%20Slowing%20down%20is%20not%20an%20option.%20The%20sector%20is%20expected%20to%20add%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Fbusiness%2Fautos%2Fchina-electric-vehicle-demand-slowing-b4e78636%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecapacity%20for%205%20million%20more%20cars%3C%2Fa%3E%20(most%20of%20them%20EVs)%20by%202025.%20Domestic%20sales%20are%20projected%20to%20reach%20only%203.7%20million%20in%20that%20same%20period.%20Sales%20for%20standout%20startups%20such%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.scmp.com%2Fbusiness%2Fchina-business%2Farticle%2F3250622%2Fchinese-ev-builders-li-auto-xpeng-and-nio-get-2024-slow-start-sharp-drop-january-sales%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENio%2C%20Li%20Auto%2C%20and%20XPeng%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20already%20coming%20in%20lower%20than%20expected.%20BYD%20alone%20has%20built%20enough%20capacity%20to%20manufacture%204%20million%20cars%20in%20China.%20In%202023%2C%20it%20sold%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.google.com%2Fsearch%3Fq%3Dhow%2Bmany%2Bcars%2Bdid%2Bbyd%2Bsell%2Bin%2B2023%26rlz%3D1C5GCEM_enUS1082US1094%26oq%3Dhow%2Bmany%2Bcars%2Bdid%2BBYD%2Bs%26gs_lcrp%3DEgZjaHJvbWUqBwgAEAAYgAQyBwgAEAAYgAQyBggBEEUYOTIHCAIQABiABDINCAMQABiGAxiABBiKBTINCAQQABiGAxiABBiKBagCALACAA%26sourceid%3Dchrome%26ie%3DUTF-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E3%20million%3C%2Fa%3E%20cars%20total.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAll%20these%20cars%20need%20somewhere%20to%20go%2C%20and%20for%20China%20EV%20Inc.%2C%20the%20more%20profitable%20option%20is%20to%20move%20them%20west%20%E2%80%94%20first%20to%20Europe%2C%20where%20trade%20barriers%20are%20easier%20to%20overcome%20(for%20now)%2C%20and%20eventually%20to%20the%20US.%20That%20is%20why%20brands%20such%20as%20BYD%2C%20Chery%2C%20and%20SAIC%20are%20all%20in%20discussions%20with%20the%20Mexican%20government%20to%20expand%20operations%20there.%20They%20need%20a%20toehold%20in%20North%20America%20to%20even%20begin%20conquering%20the%20US%20market.%20In%20the%20meantime%2C%20the%20US%20government%20is%20trying%20to%20spend%20an%20EV-parts%20ecosystem%20into%20existence%2C%20in%20part%20by%20handing%20out%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fir.novonixgroup.com%2Fnews-releases%2Fnews-release-details%2Fnovonix-finalizes-us100-million-grant-award-us-department-energy%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Egrants%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20the%20Energy%20Department%20to%20domestic%20companies%20working%20on%20battery%20technologies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENo%20country%20wants%20to%20lose%20its%20automotive%20sector%2C%20so%20in%20Brussels%20and%20Washington%2C%20the%20rise%20of%20China's%20national%20champions%20has%20become%20a%20thorny%20topic%20between%20international-trade%20interlocutors.%20In%20public%20forums%2C%20Chinese%20trade%20apparatchiks%20have%20talked%20a%20good%20game%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ft.com%2Fcontent%2F608c4b00-8efb-4322-9318-f6249096e3fe%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eabout%20culling%20excess%20capacity%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20assuage%20the%20fears%20of%20their%20counterparts.%20But%20at%20the%20same%20time%2C%20Beijing%20has%20put%20out%20an%2018-point%20plan%20to%20counter%20trade%20restrictions%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack.com%2Fredirect%2F3773ebf0-ac03-4983-8afd-9613e3ad9cbb%3Fj%3DeyJ1IjoicDBuIn0.8PdnrzqVrhaSNasEauWg-AT6mGSX3AX-3rO2hxEVAZ8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epush%20Chinese%20EVs%20out%20to%20the%20world%3C%2Fa%3E.%20None%20of%20this%20is%20really%20up%20for%20negotiation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20dominate%20the%20global%20market%2C%20Chinese%20automakers%20have%20to%20find%20ways%20to%20slip%20around%20the%20various%20barriers%20Western%20nations%20have%20put%20up.%20To%20crack%20Europe%2C%20BYD%20has%20announced%20plans%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fapnews.com%2Farticle%2Fchinas-byd-building-electric-vehicle-plant-hungary-4c4754f43703d061e1dc02516be0c14a%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebuild%20a%20factory%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20Hungary.%20Cracking%20the%20US%20is%20more%20complex.%20It%20has%20more%20trade%20barrier%20protection%20from%20a%20China%20Auto%20Inc.%20onslaught%2C%20but%20it%20may%20not%20work%20forever.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETake%2C%20for%20instance%2C%20America's%20taxes%20on%20Chinese%20EV%20imports.%20The%20Trump%20administration%20smacked%20a%2025%25%20tariff%20on%20Chinese%20EVs%2C%20bringing%20the%20total%20levy%20for%20their%20entrance%20to%20the%20US%20up%20to%2027.5%25.%20To%20avoid%20the%20tariffs%2C%20brands%20like%20BYD%2C%20Chery%2C%20and%20SAIC%20are%20all%20in%20discussions%20with%20the%20Mexican%20government%20to%20expand%20operations%20there.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMost%20likely%2C%20the%20way%20Chinese%20companies%20would%20be%20able%20to%20participate%20in%20the%20US%20EV%20market%20would%20be%20by%20investing%20in%20the%20Mexican%20auto-parts%20sector%2C%26quot%3B%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.piie.com%2Fexperts%2Fsenior-research-staff%2Fmary-e-lovely%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMary%20Lovely%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20an%20economist%20and%20senior%20fellow%20at%20the%20Peterson%20Institute%2C%20told%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EParts%20that%20come%20from%20Mexico%20would%20be%20considered%20North%20American-made%20and%20subjected%20to%20lighter%20restrictions%20under%20the%20US-Mexico-Canada%20trade%20agreement.%20EVs%20fully%20built%20in%20China%20would%20also%20not%20be%20eligible%20for%20a%20%247%2C500%20tax%20rebate%20for%20consumers%20created%20under%20President%20Joe%20Biden's%20Inflation%20Reduction%20Act.%20They%20would%20be%20eligible%2C%20though%2C%20if%20they%20were%20built%20in%20Mexico%20and%20met%20specific%20battery-sourcing%20requirements.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20some%20stakeholders%2C%20the%20barriers%20aren't%20high%20enough.%20US%20consumers%20have%20shown%20that%20if%20the%20price%20is%20low%20enough%2C%20%26quot%3BMade%20in%20America%26quot%3B%20takes%20a%20backseat.%20That's%20why%20the%20United%20Auto%20Workers%20union%20is%20already%20so%20worried%20about%20Chinese%20cars%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fselectcommitteeontheccp.house.gov%2Fsites%2Fevo-subsites%2Fselectcommitteeontheccp.house.gov%2Ffiles%2Fevo-media-document%2F11.7.2023-letter-to-ambassador-tai-auto-301.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eit%20has%20asked%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20White%20House%20to%20raise%20tariffs%20even%20more.%20The%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Feconomy%2Ftrade%2Fbiden-administration-explores-raising-tariffs-on-chinese-evs-e439d87d%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBiden%20administration%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20said%20it's%20seriously%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsubscriber.politicopro.com%2Ff%2F%3Fid%3D0000018d-1903-dc2e-a3ad-79c31af10004%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Econsidering%20such%20a%20move%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20auto%20industry%20has%20become%20caught%20up%20in%20the%20existential%20question%20that%20is%20bedeviling%20societies%20all%20over%20the%20world%20%E2%80%94%20is%20globalization%20worth%20it%3F%20In%20this%20case%3A%20What%20do%20we%20care%20about%20more%2C%20preserving%20the%20auto%20industry%20or%20giving%20consumers%20a%20variety%20of%20cheap%20EVs%20to%20choose%20from%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20want%20to%20maintain%20an%20auto%20industry%20in%20the%20US%20%E2%80%94%20that's%20essential%20for%20jobs%2C%20national%20security%2C%20and%20for%20other%20sectors%20of%20the%20economy%2C%26quot%3B%20Lovely%20said.%20%26quot%3BBut%20then%20the%20question%20is%20how%20much%20protection%20do%20you%20need%2C%20recognizing%20that%20it's%20not%20a%20free%20lunch.%20This%20is%20why%20people%20don't%20like%20economists.%20We%20keep%20reminding%20people%20none%20of%20this%20is%20free.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20no%20telling%20how%20this%20will%20all%20shake%20out.%20Sure%2C%20Chinese%20EV%20makers%20are%20lean%20and%20mean%2C%20but%20they've%20never%20had%20to%20deal%20with%20international%20markets%20before.%20Beijing%20is%20used%20to%20dealing%20with%20foreign%20brands%20entering%20its%20market%2C%20not%20the%20other%20way%20around.%20For%20most%20of%20China's%20rise%2C%20it%20has%20operated%20in%20a%20cooperative%20world.%20Now%20it's%20operating%20in%20a%20world%20where%20its%20most%20important%20trading%20partners%20no%20longer%20trust%20Beijing.%20EVs%20collect%20so%20much%20data%20that%20policymakers%20have%20started%20to%20frame%20this%20debate%20as%20one%20not%20just%20about%20trade%20but%20also%20about%20national%20security.%20That's%20a%20harder%20debate%20for%20China%20to%20win.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20US%2C%20the%20race%20to%20counter%20China%20by%20building%20a%20cheaper%20EV%20is%20on.%20Tesla%20could%20pull%20ahead%20if%20delivers%20on%20its%20promise%20to%20get%20its%20%2425%2C000%20car%20out%20by%202025.%20But%20the%20company%20has%20a%20history%20of%20delayed%20product%20launches%2C%20an%20ongoing%20price%20war%20impairing%20cash%20flow%2C%20and%20an%20erratic%2C%20X-distracted%20CEO%20to%20deal%20with.%20Big%20Auto%20is%20contending%20with%20a%20more%20muscular%20United%20Auto%20Workers%2C%20more%20skittish%20shareholders%2C%20and%20management%20that%20has%20done%20nothing%20but%20fall%20behind.%20That%20said%2C%20America's%20legacy%20automakers%20have%20experience%20fighting%20for%20their%20survival%20and%20winning.%20Whatever%20happens%2C%20what%20is%20guaranteed%20is%20a%20transformation%20of%20the%20auto%20industry.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Flinette-lopez%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3ELinette%20Lopez%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%C2%A0is%20a%20senior%20correspondent%20at%20Business%20Insider.%3C