ry%2Farticleshow%2F107979111.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia-indiatimes-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fus%2Fnikki-haley-vows-to-continue-fight-despite-trumps-win-in-south-carolina-primary%2Famp_articleshow%2F107979111.cms%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fus%2Fnikki-haley-vows-to-continue-fight-despite-trumps-win-in-south-carolina-primary%2Famp_articleshow%2F107979111.cms%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22%E2%80%98Why%20Can%E2%80%99t%20SC%20Take%20Note%20of%20Misuse%20of%20UAPA%20and%20PMLA%3F%E2%80%99%3A%20Legal%20Experts%20on%20Misuse%20of%20Laws%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F08%2F16195602%2FScreen-Shot-2021-08-16-at-7.55.39-PM.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Senior%20advocate%20Mihir%20Desai%20has%20questioned%20why%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20has%20refused%20to%20take%20note%20of%20the%20misuse%20of%20laws%20such%20as%20the%20Unlawful%20Activities%20Prevention%20Act%20(UAPA)%20and%20the%20Prevention%20of%20Money%20Laundering%20Act%20(PMLA)%20while%20addressing%20a%20seminar%20on%20the%20recent%20trends%20in%20Supreme%20Court%E2%80%99s%20judicial%20administration%2C%20management%20and%20cases%20concerning%20civil%20liberties%20and%20political%20rights%20in%20the%20national%20capital.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20seminar%20was%20held%20on%20Saturday%20(February%2024)%20and%20was%20organised%20by%20the%20Campaign%20for%20Judicial%20Accountability%20and%20Reforms%2C%20in%20collaboration%20with%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%20and%20%3Cem%3ELiveLaw%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIn%20order%20to%20crush%20dissent%2C%20one%20of%20the%20easiest%20ways%20which%20the%20government%20has%20found%20is%20to%20use%20UAPA%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Desai.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CYou%20have%20a%20situation%20where%20people%20are%20being%20put%20in%2C%20not%20because%20of%20any%20incident%20which%20has%20happened%2C%20but%20over%20suspicion.%20And%20what%20is%20the%20Supreme%20Court%E2%80%99s%20response%3F%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20referring%20to%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20taking%20note%20of%20the%20nexus%20between%20money%20and%20politics%20in%20the%20electoral%20bonds%20case%2C%20Desai%20asked%20why%20it%20can%E2%80%99t%20take%20judicial%20note%20of%20misuse%20of%20PMLA%20and%20UAPA.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWhy%20can%E2%80%99t%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20take%20judicial%20notice%20of%20the%20fact%20that%20the%20UAPA%20is%20being%20misused%3F%20Why%20can%E2%80%99t%20it%20take%20judicial%20notice%20of%20the%20fact%20that%20the%20PMLA%20is%20being%20regularly%20used%3F%20Why%20do%20you%20have%20to%20always%20bow%20down%20to%20what%20the%20solicitor%20general%20says%20even%20though%20it%20is%20not%20a%20constitutional%20post.%20Anytime%20someone%20raises%20the%20issue%20of%20Kashmir%2C%20he%20jumps%20up%20and%20says%20%E2%80%98we%20know%20on%20behalf%20of%20whom%20you%20are%20acting%2C%20on%20behalf%20of%20the%20neighbouring%20country%E2%80%99.%20But%20the%20judges%20don%E2%80%99t%20have%20the%20gumption%20to%20ask%20him%20to%20shut%20up%20and%20sit%20down.%20In%20the%20US%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20is%20known%20as%20the%20chief%20justice%E2%80%99s%20court.%20In%20India%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20should%20be%20known%20as%20Tushar%20Mehta%E2%80%99s%20court.%20That%20is%20the%20situation%20we%20have%20come%20to.%20And%20nobody%20has%20the%20guts%20to%20call%20him%20out%20and%20say%20enough%20is%20enough.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDesai%20was%20speaking%20at%20the%20second%20session%20of%20the%20seminar%20%E2%80%98The%20Supreme%20Court%E2%80%99s%20recent%20trend%20on%20cases%20involving%20Civil%20Liberties%20and%20Political%20Rights%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20issue%20of%20civil%20liberties%20and%20political%20rights%20has%20become%20critical%20amidst%20a%20surge%20in%20arrests%20of%20activists%2C%20journalists%2C%20and%20politicians%20by%20central%20agencies%20like%20the%20Enforcement%20Directorate%2C%20the%20Central%20Bureau%20of%20Investigation%2C%20and%20the%20National%20Investigation%20Authority%20on%20questionable%20grounds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20speakers%20included%20Justices%20A.K.%20Patnaik%20and%20Indira%20Banerjee%2C%20former%20judges%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%3B%20professor%20Mohan%20Gopal%2C%20former%20director%2C%20National%20Judicial%20Academy%3B%20senior%20advocates%20Trideep%20Pais%2C%20Kapil%20Sibal%3B%20and%20Warisha%20Farasat%2C%20advocate%2C%20Delhi%20high%20court%20and%20Supreme%20Court.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPais%20in%20his%20speech%20said%20that%20there%20is%20a%20%E2%80%9Cnew%20modus%E2%80%9D%20in%20the%20kind%20of%20FIRs%20that%20are%20coming%20in.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThere%20is%20a%20new%20modus%20in%20the%20kind%20of%20FIRs%20we%20deal%20with%20nowadays.%20There%20are%20certain%20persons%20who%20speak%20in%20the%20parliament%20about%20something%20they%20are%20outraged%20by%20and%20that%20is%20tweeted%20by%20some%20other%20important%20person%20and%20then%20carried%20out%20by%20new%20channels%20for%203-4%20days%2C%20by%20the%20fourth%20or%20fifth%20day%20it%20becomes%20an%20FIR.%20This%20modus%20has%20come%20to%20stay.%20This%20is%20the%20way%20a%20UAPA%20case%20comes%20to%20proceed%2C%20this%20is%20the%20pattern%20which%20I%20have%20gathered%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20Pais%20did%20not%20take%20any%20names%2C%20during%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fbjp-mp-nishikant-dubey-rahul-gandhi-newsclick-independent-journalists-chinese-links-nyt-report%5C%22%3Emonsoon%20session%20of%20parliament%2C%20BJP%20MP%20Nishikant%20Dubey%20%3C%2Fa%3Ecited%20a%20report%20by%20the%20New%20York%20Times%20in%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20to%20claim%20that%20the%20Congress%20leaders%2C%20including%20Gandhi%2C%20and%20news%20organisation%20NewsClick%20had%20received%20funds%20from%20China%20to%20create%20an%20%E2%80%9Canti-India%E2%80%9D%20atmosphere.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ENewsclick%3C%2Fem%3E%20owner%20Prabir%20Purkayastha%20has%20since%20been%20charged%20with%20UAPA%20and%20is%20in%20jail.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPais%20said%20those%20charged%20under%20UAPA%20find%20it%20more%20difficult%20to%20get%20bail%20than%20in%20PMLA%20or%20NDPS%20(Narcotics%20Drugs%20and%20Psychotropic%20Substances%20Act%20)%20cases.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EProfessor%20Gopal%20in%20his%20speech%20said%20at%20present%20the%20judgements%20on%20civil%20liberties%20and%20political%20rights%20need%20to%20be%20understood%20in%20the%20context%20of%20two%20types%20of%20judgements%20that%20are%20being%20given%20now-constitutionalist%20which%20is%20ingrained%20in%20the%20Constitution%20and%20theocratic%20judgements%20where%20the%20comes%20from%20the%20belief%20that%20we%20have%20to%20go%20beyond%20the%20constitution%20into%20religion%20to%20give%20judgements.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EReferring%20to%20the%20Ayodhya%20title%20dispute%20judgement%20and%20the%20hijab%20judgement%2C%20Gopal%20said%20that%20the%20Indian%20polity%20where%20religion%20has%20no%20space%2C%20idols%20are%20being%20brought%20in%20through%20these%20theocratic%20judgements.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CImagine%20an%20edifice%20structure%20%E2%80%93%20our%20polity%20where%20religion%20has%20no%20space%20and%20most%20sacred%20foundation%20is%20the%20belief%20that%20all%20power%20comes%20from%20the%20people%2C%20and%20into%20that%20space%20you%20are%20bringing%20in%20idols%2C%20through%20these%20idols%20through%20these%20theocratic%20judgements.%20It%20may%20take%20half%20a%20century%20to%20change%2C%20bring%20down%20these%20structures%20and%20to%20construct%20a%20new%20theological%20state%20and%20that%20construction%20is%20going%20on%20presently%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFarasat%20said%20that%20bail%20jurisprudence%20and%20how%20investigations%20are%20taking%20place%20especially%20in%20the%20Delhi%20riots%20cases%2C%20Bhima%20Koregaon%20cases%20or%20in%20Newsclick%20case%20shows%20that%20police%20are%20not%20acting%20in%20good%20faith.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20moment%20a%20client%20booked%20under%20UAPA%20walks%20in%20to%20my%20office%2C%20we%20advise%20that%20we%20will%20move%20for%20bail%20after%206%20months%2C%20that%E2%80%99s%20how%20were%20are%20advising%20now.%20We%20are%20in%20a%20very%20serious%20situation.%20We%20say%20let%E2%80%99s%20not%20do%20anything%20until%20chargesheet%20is%20filed.%20We%20are%20starting%20at%20a%20point%20of%20loss%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EReferring%20to%20the%20%3Cem%3ENewsclick%3C%2Fem%3E%20case%2C%20she%20said%20that%20a%20%E2%80%9Clazy%20line%20in%20%3Cem%3EThe%20New%20York%20Times%E2%80%9D%20%3C%2Fem%3Ehas%20the%20owner%20in%20jail.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CEven%20when%20we%20look%20at%20terror%20cases%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20does%20have%20a%20tendency%20to%20be%20fair.%20The%20jurisprudence%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20until%20recently%20was%20about%20liberty%20and%20was%20leaning%20towards%20giving%20people%20their%20liberty%20no%20matter%20what%20the%20offence%20was.%20I%20think%20those%20days%20are%20now%20gone.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESibal%20in%20his%20speech%20said%20that%20it%20is%20time%20to%20question%20the%20genesis%20of%20this%20law%20of%20CRPC%20and%20IPC%20which%20were%20derived%20from%20British%20colonial%20laws%20which%20were%20used%20to%20quell%20dissent%20simply%20on%20the%20grounds%20of%20suspicion.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWhen%20the%20British%20had%20this%20provision%20that%20you%20can%20arrest%20anybody%20on%20the%20basis%20of%20suspicion-why%20did%20they%20do%20it%3F%20Because%20they%20wanted%20to%20quell%20dissent%20and%20stop%20anybody%20to%20talk%20against%20the%20British%20government.%20How%20does%20this%20provision%20pass%20the%20test%20of%20constitutionality%3F%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CI%20can%20suspect%20anybody.%20What%20is%20the%20basis%3F%20That%20is%20subjective.%20It%20cannot%20be%20objective.%20There%20is%20no%20procedure%20to%20make%20it%20objective%20in%20CRPC.%20I%20have%20a%20problem%20with%20the%20genesis%20of%20criminal%20procedure.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESibal%20said%20in%20PMLA%20and%20ED%20cases%2C%20arrests%20are%20made%20under%20suspicion%20and%20reasons%20for%20summons%20and%20offences%20are%20not%20disclosed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CHave%20I%20no%20right%20to%20know%3F%20I%20am%20not%20talking%20about%20cases%20where%20there%20is%20a%20murder%20there%20are%20eyewitnesses.%20In%20these%20so%20called%20economic%20offences%20and%20offences%20against%20the%20state%20as%20in%20UAPA%20and%20PMLA%20which%20have%20draconian%20provisions%20which%20according%20to%20me%20are%20entirely%20unconstitutional.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJustice%20Patnaik%20in%20his%20remarks%20said%20that%20the%20most%20important%20qualification%20of%20a%20judge%20is%20%E2%80%9Ccommitment%20to%20civil%20liberties.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CJudges%20should%20be%20sensitive.%20The%20most%20important%20qualification%20of%20a%20judge%20is%20the%20commitment%20to%20protect%20the%20rights%20of%20civil%20liberties%20of%20the%20individuals.%20Second%2C%20you%20must%20have%20a%20very%20independent%20bar%20%E2%80%93%20not%20only%20for%20the%20executive%20but%20also%20from%20the%20judges.%20Flattery%20of%20a%20judge%20has%20to%20be%20avoided%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20added%20that%20judges%20should%20also%20read%2C%20and%20added%20that%20he%20had%20%E2%80%9Cimproved%20judgements%20after%20reading.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1708834274000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F08%2F16195602%2FScreen-Shot-2021-08-16-at-7.55.39-PM.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fwhy-cant-sc-take-note-of-misuse-of-uapa-and-pmla-legal-experts-on-misuse-of-laws%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22In%20his%20remarks%20at%20a%20seminar%20organised%